Immediate media upload: fix inspector photos not reaching PM view

Root cause: When the inspector captured photos on mobile, File objects were
stored only in browser memory (as blob URLs). If the browser restarted
(camera trigger issue), File objects serialized to empty {} in localStorage.
On submission, formData.append('media_N', {}) sent nothing, so no media
records were created in the database.

Fix:
- Added /api/media/upload-temp endpoint for immediate file uploads
- Photos/videos are now uploaded to the server immediately when captured,
  not waiting for final form submission
- MediaPreview interface extended with uploadedUrl and uploading fields
- On submission, pre-uploaded URLs are passed via mediaUrl_N fields
  instead of re-uploading the File object
- Draft restore filters out media with invalid/empty File objects
  and uses uploadedUrl for preview when available
- Upload status indicators: spinning loader during upload, green checkmark
  when successfully uploaded to server

Security hardening (per code review):
- Server validates pre-uploaded URLs: must start with /uploads/, no path
  traversal, and file must exist on disk
- Temp upload endpoint restricts to image/video MIME types only
- Applied to all three submission handlers: full inspection, onboarding
  inspection, and issues
